            <h2 id="part-2" class="no-margins">
              Infra-red (IR) assistive-listening systems deliver clear speech
              intelligibility in theatres, conference rooms, and training spaces
              by<span class="light-accent">
                transmitting audio directly to headsets or hearing-aid
                receivers.</span
              >
            </h2>
            <div class="spacer-sm"></div>
            <div class="section-divider home-c-numbers"></div>

            <h5>
              The focused IR signal minimises ambient noise and bypasses
              electrical interference. This can be an advantage when induction
              loops are impractical or privacy is a factor.
            </h5>

            <h5>
              Infrared receivers can either be used with headphones or a
              neck-loop to connect to a hearing aid / cochlear implant via <a
                href="#telecoil"
                class="teal-text">telecoil (T-Coil)</a
              >.
            </h5>
